00:12:42,879 --> 00:12:45,709
We're going to be shooting
a commercial!

221
00:12:47,049 --> 00:12:48,039
What?

222
00:12:48,719 --> 00:12:49,879
Ohmori Electronics

223
00:12:52,119 --> 00:12:54,459
T-This shop is...

224
00:12:54,559 --> 00:13:00,259
The manager is a really good person.
And he's a nice guy.

225
00:13:00,399 --> 00:13:05,959
Umm... They've been around since
current owner Eijirou's grandfather.

226
00:13:06,539 --> 00:13:10,739
You can find anything from batteries
to refrigerators here.

227
00:13:11,539 --> 00:13:12,979
Umm... well...

228
00:13:13,379 --> 00:13:17,339
In any case, please come by
Ohmori Electronics!

229
00:13:17,479 --> 00:13:19,009
Okay, cut!

230
00:13:20,079 --> 00:13:22,479
Hmm, I just don't feel
the emotion...

231
00:13:22,619 --> 00:13:24,989
I wonder why that is...

232
00:13:25,319 --> 00:13:27,219
Mama, what's that?

233
00:13:27,359 --> 00:13:29,349
Shh, you mustn't look.

234
00:13:29,689 --> 00:13:30,559
I've got it!

235
00:13:30,699 --> 00:13:32,889
For the love of God, please
don't "get" anything else!

236
00:13:34,169 --> 00:13:37,189
It doesn't make sense for a waitress
to be at an electronics store.

237
00:13:37,299 --> 00:13:38,359
That's "it"!?

238
00:13:38,499 --> 00:13:41,059
Koizumi, hand me
the small bag over there!

239
00:13:41,309 --> 00:13:42,029
Yes, ma'am.

240
00:13:42,809 --> 00:13:46,269
"Let me have a camera, and I'll put a
commercial for your store in my movie."

241
00:13:46,409 --> 00:13:47,669
"Sure thing."

242
00:13:47,809 --> 00:13:51,539
That's probably the conversation Haruhi
had with the owner in five seconds.

243
00:13:52,879 --> 00:13:54,349
Mikuru, come here
a second.

244
00:13:55,319 --> 00:13:59,259
Oh my. It doesn't look like I'll
have any lines in this part.

245
00:14:00,359 --> 00:14:06,089
Actually, I'm one of the actors in
my class's stage production, too.

246
00:14:06,229 --> 00:14:08,859
I'm having quite a hard time
remembering all of the lines.

247
00:14:08,999 --> 00:14:10,229
Oh really.

248
00:14:10,369 --> 00:14:14,399
I'd prefer it if my role for this
was light on lines, but...

249
00:14:14,539 --> 00:14:17,339
How about if you take
the lead role?

250
00:14:17,479 --> 00:14:20,239
Haruhi's the one controlling
the casting.

251
00:14:20,379 --> 00:14:23,139
Ask her if you want
to switch.

252
00:14:23,279 --> 00:14:26,809
Do you really think that I could do
something as frightening as that?

253
00:14:27,149 --> 00:14:29,809
These are Miss Suzumiya's
orders after all,

254
00:14:29,949 --> 00:14:34,519
and I'd rather not imagine what would
await me if I disobeyed them.

255
00:14:34,859 --> 00:14:39,919
I'd rather not, either. That's why
I'm sitting here as the cameraman.

256
00:14:40,199 --> 00:14:41,599
And we're back!

257
00:14:44,739 --> 00:14:47,099
It's Miss Asahina's first costume
from a while back.

258
00:14:47,309 --> 00:14:49,539
A perfect bunny girl.

259
00:14:50,609 --> 00:14:53,099
Oh yeah, that was over
half a year ago.

260
00:14:53,239 --> 00:14:55,469
Now that I think about it,
quite a bit happened then.

261
00:14:55,949 --> 00:14:58,539
Right now,
they're fond memories...

262
00:14:59,479 --> 00:15:00,849
As if!

263
00:15:00,989 --> 00:15:02,979
Okay, this is perfect!

264
00:15:03,119 --> 00:15:05,919
A bunny girl really is the best fit
for introducing a product.

265
00:15:06,089 --> 00:15:08,079
Okay, we're going to take it
from the top!

266
00:15:08,459 --> 00:15:10,189
Kyon, get the
camera ready!

267
00:15:11,829 --> 00:15:13,759
All right,
this is take two!

268
00:15:15,599 --> 00:15:18,999
And so, the commercial for the
electronics store was finished.

269
00:15:19,599 --> 00:15:22,899
There's one thing you need
to remember, though.

270
00:15:23,069 --> 00:15:26,239
There was one other sponsor
that we visited last time.

271
00:15:26,239 --> 00:15:27,709
Yamatsuchi Model Shop

272
00:15:29,149 --> 00:15:31,049
All right.
Okay then, Mikuru.

273
00:15:31,379 --> 00:15:33,209
Do it just like you did
at the other store!

274
00:15:33,349 --> 00:15:34,719
There were no problems
that time!

275
00:15:35,049 --> 00:15:36,609
Like hell there weren't.

276
00:15:36,749 --> 00:15:39,049
Okay, action!

277
00:15:39,989 --> 00:15:44,219
T-This model shop opened
for business last year

278
00:15:44,359 --> 00:15:47,889
after Mr. Keiji Yamatsuchi, age 28,
left his corporate job.

279
00:15:48,499 --> 00:15:52,629
It's like his hobbies took over
his actions, and he just did it.

280
00:15:53,369 --> 00:15:57,169
And as many thought,
sales haven't met expectations...

281
00:15:57,609 --> 00:16:06,239
The first-half earnings this year
are down 80% from last year...

282
00:16:06,619 --> 00:16:09,139
So shop as much
as you can, everyone!

283
00:16:13,419 --> 00:16:14,859
You want me
to hold it?

284
00:16:21,629 --> 00:16:24,259
D-Don't shoot while pointing
at people!

285
00:16:24,399 --> 00:16:27,059
Hold off by shooting things
like empty cans!

286
00:16:27,839 --> 00:16:29,029
You want me
to shoot?

287
00:16:32,779 --> 00:16:34,639
All right, cut!

288
00:16:35,679 --> 00:16:38,169
Today's filming
was only so-so.

289
00:16:38,319 --> 00:16:40,809
But tomorrow we're going to start
shooting the movie itself.

290
00:16:41,289 --> 00:16:44,689
We've already added fifteen minutes
to the movie with the commercials.

291
00:16:44,819 --> 00:16:46,789
How long is the actual movie
going to be?

292
00:16:46,919 --> 00:16:50,419
Well, we'll just shoot as much as
we can and edit it down later.

293
00:16:50,559 --> 00:16:52,859
These days, it's a snap
with a computer.

294
00:16:52,929 --> 00:16:54,989
And who's going to be doing
the snapping?

295
00:16:55,129 --> 00:16:58,859
I've got the feeling that "editor" was
one of the things listed under my jobs.

296
00:16:59,269 --> 00:17:01,199
Tomorrow's Saturday,
and a day off from school,

297
00:17:01,339 --> 00:17:03,139
so I want everyone
to show up!

298
00:17:03,269 --> 00:17:06,179
Be at Kitaguchi Station
at nine o'clock!

299
00:17:06,309 --> 00:17:10,769
Hey, Haruhi. Can't you do something
about Miss Asahina's outfit?

300
00:17:11,719 --> 00:17:15,479
There has to be a more appropriate
outfit for someone who fights.

301
00:17:15,649 --> 00:17:17,919
You know, like a plug suit
or a stealth suit or something.

302
00:17:19,559 --> 00:17:20,649
Tsk tsk.

303
00:17:21,259 --> 00:17:24,059
If she wore something like that,
there'd be no unpredictability.

304
00:17:24,159 --> 00:17:25,749
The audience will be surprised
and go "whoa!"

305
00:17:25,859 --> 00:17:28,199
Because it's a waitress
that's fighting.

306
00:17:28,329 --> 00:17:30,059
Being able to grab the
audience is vital!

307
00:17:30,169 --> 00:17:31,859
That's the concept,
you know!

308
00:17:32,169 --> 00:17:35,199
I wonder if she understands the
meaning of the word "concept."

309
00:17:35,739 --> 00:17:40,539
Well, never mind that, then.
Why is she here from the future?

310
00:17:41,509 --> 00:17:43,279
Well, that is, you know.

311
00:17:43,409 --> 00:17:46,539
Umm, the character doesn't have
to be from the future, right?

312
00:17:46,679 --> 00:17:47,739
It's all right!

313
00:17:47,889 --> 00:17:51,049
We'll figure that out
when the time comes!

314
00:17:51,419 --> 00:17:54,549
And if we can't think of something,
then we'll just ignore it!

315
00:17:54,759 --> 00:17:57,189
As long as it's amusing,
it's fine!

316
00:17:59,099 --> 00:18:01,529
That's only if it's
amusing though, right?

317
00:18:02,499 --> 00:18:05,329
It's not much good if only the
director finds it amusing!

318
00:18:05,469 --> 00:18:08,699
Are you trying to get the Golden
Raspberry award for non-pros?

319
00:18:08,839 --> 00:18:11,399
What are you talking about?
There's only one thing we're going for.

320
00:18:11,509 --> 00:18:14,439
That's the "best of the festival"
for the school festival!

321
00:18:14,579 --> 00:18:17,139
And if we can,
the Golden Globe, too!

322
00:18:17,679 --> 00:18:20,709
All right, then. At least show me
the script. How's it coming along?

323
00:18:22,089 --> 00:18:23,349
No problem!

324
00:18:23,489 --> 00:18:28,359
It's all up here. The script and the
storyboards are all ready to go!

325
00:18:28,829 --> 00:18:31,389
You don't have to think
about a thing.

326
00:18:32,399 --> 00:18:34,729
Well, that's just great.

327
00:18:34,869 --> 00:18:36,729
You don't need to think
about anything, either.

328
00:18:36,799 --> 00:18:38,889
You just need to sit and
stare out the window.

329
00:18:39,039 --> 00:18:43,559
As long as you had a pleasant look on your
face, you'd be as cute as Miss Asahina.

330
00:18:44,209 --> 00:18:45,139
What?

331
00:18:45,279 --> 00:18:46,399
Nothing.

332
00:18:46,509 --> 00:18:48,999
Okay, everyone.
We're going to get fired up!

333
00:18:49,149 --> 00:18:51,939
You need to be idealistic if you
want to capture any glory.

334
00:18:52,349 --> 00:18:55,219
When you free yourself of your inhibitions,
the latent abilities

335
00:18:55,349 --> 00:18:59,289
within you will awaken,
revealing unimaginable powers!

336
00:19:00,059 --> 00:19:03,289
This isn't a counterattack like you'd
see in a battle manga, you know...

337
00:19:06,329 --> 00:19:07,159
- It's a balloon!
- Oh, you're right.

338
00:19:07,159 --> 00:19:08,629
- It's a balloon!
- Oh, you're right.
The next morning.

339
00:19:08,969 --> 00:19:13,839
As of today, we've fallen
into a strange situation.

340
00:19:13,969 --> 00:19:16,599
No, how can I
put this?

341
00:19:16,739 --> 00:19:17,509
What did Haruhi say?
Something like,

342
00:19:17,509 --> 00:19:19,209
Mommy, how far will the balloon go?
Huh? Huh?
What did Haruhi say?
Something like,

343
00:19:19,209 --> 00:19:19,309
Mommy, how far will the balloon go?
Huh? Huh?

344
00:19:19,309 --> 00:19:22,049
Mommy, how far will the balloon go?
Huh? Huh?
"When you free yourself of your
inhibitions, the latent abilities

345
00:19:22,049 --> 00:19:22,879
Well, pretty far.
"When you free yourself of your
inhibitions, the latent abilities

346
00:19:22,879 --> 00:19:22,979
Well, pretty far.

347
00:19:22,979 --> 00:19:24,519
Well, pretty far.
Within you will awaken,
revealing unimaginable powers!"

348
00:19:24,519 --> 00:19:26,419
Within you will awaken,
revealing unimaginable powers!"

349
00:19:26,819 --> 00:19:27,419
Huh? Pretty far?

350
00:19:27,419 --> 00:19:29,619
Huh? Pretty far?
But Haruhi, the one gaining
powers won't be you.

351
00:19:29,619 --> 00:19:32,049
But Haruhi, the one gaining
powers won't be you.

352
00:19:32,319 --> 00:19:34,549
And you won't
even know it.

353
00:19:35,629 --> 00:19:37,059
You're late!

354
00:19:37,189 --> 00:19:38,989
It's not even nine yet.

355
00:19:39,159 --> 00:19:43,459
You're still last. As punishment,
you're buying us lunch.

356
00:19:43,669 --> 00:19:44,859
Yeah, yeah.

357
00:19:51,079 --> 00:19:55,509
Well, I'll cover the bus fare!
It's part of our necessary expenses!

358
00:19:56,209 --> 00:19:57,269
Thanks.

359
00:19:57,509 --> 00:19:58,239
Oh yeah!

360
00:19:58,349 --> 00:20:00,079
I need to put this on...

361
00:20:01,349 --> 00:20:03,549
Why are you wearing
your school uniform?

362
00:20:04,149 --> 00:20:06,319
She told me to
wear it yesterday.

363
00:20:06,519 --> 00:20:13,019
It's because I'm playing a high school
student who has psychic powers.

364
00:20:13,129 --> 00:20:14,759
So you're just
playing yourself.

365
00:20:14,899 --> 00:20:16,259
All right, this works!

366
00:20:16,529 --> 00:20:18,399
Okay, the bus stop
is this way!

367
00:20:18,399 --> 00:20:18,799
Super Director
Okay, the bus stop
