368
00:20:18,799 --> 00:20:19,969
Super Director
Come on, Kyon,
hurry up!

369
00:20:19,969 --> 00:20:20,699
Come on, Kyon,
hurry up!

370
00:20:24,169 --> 00:20:26,169
After thirty minutes of
being shaken by the bus

371
00:20:26,339 --> 00:20:28,399
and thirty minutes
of walking,

372
00:20:28,549 --> 00:20:31,239
we ended up in a place
that would make you ask,

373
00:20:31,379 --> 00:20:33,509
"Why did we come to a place
no one wants to come to?"

374
00:20:34,219 --> 00:20:35,479
Man, it's hot...

375
00:20:35,619 --> 00:20:36,979
Umm...

376
00:20:37,319 --> 00:20:40,849
Would you like some of mine?
If you don't mind that it's half-drunk...

377
00:20:41,129 --> 00:20:43,059
Half-drunk?
Oh, thank you.

378
00:20:45,599 --> 00:20:48,789
Take care of that later!
You too, Mikuru!

379
00:20:49,129 --> 00:20:53,089
There's no time to give our gofer
a drink break!

380
00:20:53,239 --> 00:20:56,569
Come on, we're going to
start shooting. Get changed!

381
00:20:57,039 --> 00:20:57,699
But...

382
00:20:57,779 --> 00:21:00,769
It's fine! If you go far enough in,
you won't run into anyone!

383
00:21:03,209 --> 00:21:04,509
The half-drunk...

384
00:21:06,779 --> 00:21:08,749
- Don't peek.
- Right.

385
00:21:10,689 --> 00:21:13,419
Ta-dah!
It's a color contact.

386
00:21:13,689 --> 00:21:17,529
Having different colored eyes
is pretty important, you know!

387
00:21:18,029 --> 00:21:21,019
One differently colored eye will
increase the sense of mystery!

388
00:21:21,269 --> 00:21:23,059
It's symbolic!

389
00:21:23,969 --> 00:21:26,629
And there's a secret
in this blue eye of hers!

390
00:21:26,739 --> 00:21:30,399
Well, it'd make no sense for her to
just have a differently colored eye.

391
00:21:30,509 --> 00:21:32,439
So? What's the secret?

392
00:21:33,639 --> 00:21:35,079
It's still a secret!

393
00:21:35,479 --> 00:21:38,709
Come on, Mikuru, how long are
you going to loaf about?

394
00:21:40,779 --> 00:21:44,519
Hey! Mikuru!
Stop being so embarrassed!

395
00:21:44,719 --> 00:21:47,319
You just need to get
into your character!

396
00:21:50,129 --> 00:21:52,359
Okay, try running
one more time.

397
00:21:55,799 --> 00:21:58,999
It looks like this is our opening
sequence, worthy of celebration.

398
00:21:59,339 --> 00:22:01,829
I thought that she'd at least
write a script or something,

399
00:22:01,939 --> 00:22:04,569
but Haruhi simply declared
that there wasn't one.

400
00:22:05,409 --> 00:22:08,609
We'd be in big trouble if I wrote
it down and it got leaked.

401
00:22:08,749 --> 00:22:10,649
That's the reason
she gave.

402
00:22:10,749 --> 00:22:12,909
I wonder when this turned
into a Hong Kong flick.

403
00:22:13,049 --> 00:22:15,879
Okay! Once more, like you
did the third time!

404
00:22:18,319 --> 00:22:21,619
Okay, next up is the fight scene
between Mikuru and Yuki!

405
00:22:22,089 --> 00:22:24,959
Mikuru, shoot at Yuki
with all you've got!

406
00:22:25,999 --> 00:22:28,689
But didn't they say to not
point these at people?

407
00:22:28,799 --> 00:22:32,629
It's all right. There's no
way you'll hit her, Mikuru!

408
00:22:32,999 --> 00:22:35,939
And if it looks like she'd get hit,
Yuki will be able to dodge it.

409
00:22:37,369 --> 00:22:39,899
It's all right.
Fire.

410
00:22:40,039 --> 00:22:42,739
See? She said it's all right!
Shoot her up!

411
00:22:42,879 --> 00:22:46,209
Oh yeah, don't fire them at the
same time, but one after the other!

412
00:22:46,349 --> 00:22:48,719
That's one of the basics
of two-gun fighting!

413
00:22:57,329 --> 00:22:59,159
Yeah. I guess
this works.

414
00:23:00,399 --> 00:23:05,629
Hey, Haruhi. How is this a movie?
I have no idea what's going on.

415
00:23:05,769 --> 00:23:10,229
That's fine! We'll just cut and paste it
together during editing.

416
00:23:10,409 --> 00:23:13,339
And who's going to do that?
That cutting and pasting?

417
00:23:13,639 --> 00:23:15,539
At least put in
some dialog.

418
00:23:15,909 --> 00:23:19,909
It's fine! If we have to, we'll mute the
sound and record the dialog afterwards!

419
00:23:20,019 --> 00:23:23,179
We have to put in sound effects
and background music, anyways!

420
00:23:23,589 --> 00:23:26,219
You don't have to think
too hard about this!

421
00:23:28,459 --> 00:23:32,719
Even if we wanted to,
the story is only in your head,

422
00:23:32,859 --> 00:23:36,029
so there's nothing for us
to think about.

423
00:23:44,069 --> 00:23:46,639
Sora kara ochite kitanda
It fell from the sky

424
00:23:46,639 --> 00:23:49,349
Subete no negai wo nosete
With all of the wishes
that were made upon it

425
00:23:49,349 --> 00:23:53,869
Hitotsu no hoshi niwa
chotto omokatta kana
Maybe it was a little too heavy
for a single star

426
00:23:54,549 --> 00:23:57,149
Yappari nanika henda yo
Something just doesn't
seem right

427
00:23:57,149 --> 00:23:59,789
Kokoro no kimi ga kieta
The image of you in my mind
has vanished

428
00:23:59,789 --> 00:24:03,989
Tashika ni oboeteru tte
ieruno kai?
Can I say that I
remember you clearly?

429
00:24:03,989 --> 00:24:05,529
Tomare!
Stop!

430
00:24:05,529 --> 00:24:09,299
Kako wa jibun no mono
The past belongs to me

431
00:24:09,299 --> 00:24:14,069
Touzen daretomo torikaetakunai
Of course I don't want to trade it
with anyone else

432
00:24:14,069 --> 00:24:15,209
Nazenara
That's because

433
00:24:15,209 --> 00:24:20,439
Basudei datta watashitachi niwa
It was my birthday,
and when we saw each other

434
00:24:20,439 --> 00:24:23,209
Deai ga umareta toki ni
We could see the first dream

435
00:24:23,209 --> 00:24:25,649
Hajimete no yume ga mieru
That we had
when we were born

436
00:24:25,649 --> 00:24:30,489
Doushiyouka tte
nayanda koto mo
Worrying about
"what do I do?"

437
00:24:30,489 --> 00:24:34,389
Ima omoeba waraeru hodo
datta yo ne
Is laughable when I
think about it now

438
00:24:34,389 --> 00:24:37,089
Mou wasureteta
I've already forgotten it

439
00:24:37,089 --> 00:24:39,189
Kimi wo sagasou
Let's search for you

